<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="335" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,706,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
Description of the 
<typeStatus box="[428,532,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">holotype</typeStatus>
, female. Body
</emphasis>
: 7.6 x 
<quantity box="[793,882,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" unit="mm" value="4.4">4.4 mm</quantity>
(length with head extended x maximum width) Medium and somewhat flattened. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[546,610,260,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Head</emphasis>
: Clypeal teeth medium, pointing upwards; and separated by a rounded indentation that is slightly more the length of the teeth; very small notch on lateral margin where genal suture terminates; frontal suture effaced; clypeal surface densely punctate with very few irregular setae; eyes narrowing posteriorly; antennae dark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Pronotum:</emphasis>
Surface shagreened and densely punctate with round punctures and a few short black setae; shallow medial basal depression with punctures terminating into a short puncture free line, no lateral foveae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,284,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Elytra:</emphasis>
Striae distinct, punctate, with clear double margins; interstriae with small granules and irregular short black setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,1242,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,548,573]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Pygidium:</emphasis>
Shagreened with irregular, short, black, recurved setae; ventrite densely punctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Venter:</emphasis>
Metaventrite punctures large and almost touching posteriorly, becoming smaller and more separated anteriorly; mesoventrite punctures irregularly shaped and arranged, almost touching.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,543,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Not available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1284,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,1284,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Etymology:</emphasis>
In the species name, the Latinised prefix “ 
<emphasis box="[817,893,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">inpar”</emphasis>
translates to “unequal” in English.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="335" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,727,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<emphasis box="[684,813,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scholtz &amp; Howden" authorityYear="1987" box="[684,809,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">E. rugosus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel, 2019" authorityName="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel" authorityYear="2019" box="[939,1121,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inparrugosus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[939,1121,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. inparrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1130,1266,727,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be readily identified by its round, slightly-separated, pronotal punctures. In 
<emphasis box="[883,1010,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scholtz &amp; Howden" authorityYear="1987" box="[883,1005,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">E. rugosus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
the pronotal punctures are irregularly shaped and touching one another. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel, 2019" authorityName="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel" authorityYear="2019" box="[691,872,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inparrugosus" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[691,872,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. inparrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[880,1015,799,824]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
shows a mountain distribution in the Swartberg of the 
<collectingRegion box="[344,493,836,860]" country="South Africa" name="Eastern Cape" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Eastern Cape</collectingRegion>
compared to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scholtz &amp; Howden" authorityYear="1987" box="[645,765,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis box="[645,765,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that shows a range in the Cedarberg of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1251,1410,836,860]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Western Cape</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="335" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,871,896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Remarks:</emphasis>
The single 
<typeStatus box="[450,546,872,896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">paratype</typeStatus>
had been previously designated as a 
<typeStatus box="[965,1061,872,896]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scholtz &amp; Howden" authorityYear="1987" box="[1100,1220,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1220,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is clearly not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scholtz &amp; Howden" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. rugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and belongs to this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="335" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,969,943,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">Distribution, ecology, conservation status, and potential threats:</emphasis>
This species is probably restricted to the Swartberg mountain range where it has been recorded in the Fynbos Biome. Based on limited distribution data, 
<taxonomicName authority="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel, 2019" authorityName="Deschodt &amp; Davis &amp; Daniel" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Epirinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inparrugosus" status="new species">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="335">E. inparrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[309,445,1015,1040]" pageId="8" pageNumber="335" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
is assessed as data deficient (DD). However, it is well protected in the Swartberg East Nature Reserve and an adjacent cluster of reserves in the Swartberg.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
